    "Regarding the absolute values, it may be observed that the production peaks refer to the periods of the Roman Empire and the Contemporary Age, becoming increasingly frequent towards the present.",
    "These periods coincide with those with the lowest relative usage of reCon3D.Figure 9 displays the same data as Fig. 8, but it separates the sample by heritage type instead of by RP.",
    "In this case, the most frequent types of heritage were Civil Heritage, representing 33% of the cases, followed by Urban Heritage (29%), and Sacred Heritage (21%).",
    "This can be seen in Fig. 9, where Civil Heritage is concentrated in the period of the Roman Empire and the Modern and Contemporary Age, which are the periods with the highest frequency of cases.",
    "Industrial Heritage also shows significant importance in those last two periods."
